                <h4>Complementary Courses (30 credits)</h4>

    
              <p>30 credits selected as described below.</p>
<p>In addition to the 6-credit requirement for Advanced Study described below, all Joint Honours students' programs of study shall include 6 credits of study at the 400 level or above. Students are encouraged to take courses at the 300 level and above.</p>
<p>Note on Topics Courses: The Department of English offers courses which change topic from academic year to academic year.  Depending on the topic in a specific year, these courses may count toward different program requirements.  At the time they register for a topics course, students should confirm with their program adviser the program requirement it fulfils for that academic year.</p>
    
      
      
                <h4>Advanced Study</h4>

    
              <p>6 credits of advanced study, in one of the following two forms A or B, in order of preference:</p>
    
      
      
                <h4></h4>

    
