                <h4></h4>

    
              <p>B) Two 3-credit 500-level courses selected in consultation with the student's adviser(s).</p>
    
      
      
                <h4></h4>

    
              <p>(In very rare cases, a third alternative may be approved at the discretion of the Joint Honours Adviser, but only when it is formally recommended for the joint subject according to the description of that Joint Honours program found in the Arts section of the eCalendar. For example, Joint Honours with Anthropology allows the option of combining 3 credits of essay work with 3 credits in the joint subject to create a joint essay.)</p>
    
      
      
